Umar Muhammed, Lafia The National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party has inaugurated a caretaker committee for Nasarawa State. In a letter with reference no. PDP/DOM/GF.2/VOL.1A/20/096(B), dated July 2nd, 2020, copied to Chairman of the Zonal Working Committee, Mr. Theophilus Shan’s made available to The Punch, in Lafia on Sunday, the PDP  directed Dakas to take charge and oversee the activities of the Nasarawa State chapter of the party until further notice. The letter, which was signed by the party’s National Organising Secretary,  Col. Austine Akobundu (retd.), read, “This is to formally inform you that the National Working Committee of our great party, Peoples Democratic Party, has directed that you and your zonal Working committee should perform your constitutional duty by overseeing the activities of the Nasarawa State chapter of our party until further notice, pursuant to section 26(2)(a) and (b) of our party’s constitution (2017 as amended) and  any other function that may be assigned to you by the National Executive Committee through the National Working Committee.” The letter also directed the ZWC to maintain strict oversight on the conduct of the party’s primary for the purpose of nominating the flagbearer for the Nasarawa central state constituency by- election on August 8. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 